		<table width="100%">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    How to be a good wizard at levels 1 - 20 (even though,it has to be 1 - 35)</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:linda2193@yahoo.com">Hermony</a> | 
		            4/3/2001 2:10:58 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">Chapter 1 <BR>
            How to start as a newbie<BR>
  You are now here to learn how to be a good wizard.As a newbie wizard,you got your dagger and your robe and your spells.You kill bats,wasp,skeleton etc. You cast Frost Bolt first,then once they get to you,you start piercing the npc (Non-Player Character). Once it runs away,you cast any lvl 1 spell to it to finish it.<BR>
                    Chapter 2<BR>
              At level 5-10...<BR>
   Once you are level 5,there is something you have to learn at level 5.You must now group.You not in newbie spot no more.You must now kill orcs with members.And when you group with members,they will try not to make anybody die.But in a group all they doing is trying to get used to in a group and work together to kill that one thing.You do the same thing all over again until level 7. At level 7,you go start going to CB (CrushBone) and go find a group.Just like doing it in greater faydark but only in a place where bunch of orcs are.It is really dangerous to go by yourself in CB.You will die easily without a group.and since you still have level 4 spells,while you fight with your group in CB,you root stuff and start blasting. DO NOT go and pierce the orc when you are in a group.Someone maybe already doing the fighting job and your job is to root it and start blasting until they have damaged.When you are lvl 8,you get spells but you still use your root.And do same thing until lvl 10.<BR>
                   Chapter 3<BR>
              Level 10-15...<BR>
  Levels 11-15 maybe a little easier.You may still be in CB and kill the higher level stuff.But still do the same thing every time you get a different spell,still use your root! And be in groups.But sometimes you can solo if you can handle some orcs.But at this level,you should head to Qeynos and go to the boat to Erud's Crossing.Over there,there are willow wisp that you can kill by yourself.They can hit hard.Use your root and start blasting.SOMETIMES YOU MAY TO ATTACK IT.But remember,maybe you should go to this place at lvl 12 once you get your new spells and you bind yourself.Anyways,you can solo at wisp island (Erud's Crossing) or go to Warrens.That place can be dangerous when you try to find it.and once your at level 15 you  keep doing warrens or...<BR>
                  Chapter 4<BR>
                 15-20...<BR>
 Oasis.At 15 you may start doing Oasis.You kill caimans or get in an orc group.You easily level fast.When you are in group or even if you are soloing.But once your at 16,you still kill caimans,and ALWAYS use your root.Anything that cons white or blue you may handle only.Things in Oasis is rough.It's better in a group though.Its better experience and may take 5 or 3 days to get to 20.By grouping or soloing.But grouping is better experince.At level 16,don't forget you also get new spells.And at 20 you get your Enstill (another root spell,but just for a waste of mana,but may work) that you can use that or your lvl 4 root still.<BR>
                   Chapter 5<BR>
            20-25 is the matter right now.<BR>
   Levels 20 and up is the greatest of all.You get better spells and plus,you get to teleport where ever you want. (Unless you pass levels 20-24 than you get everywhere you want).At level 20 you either start going to SK (South Karana) Or go to highpass and hunt orcs down and maybe soon highkeep.You always do the same thing.In South Karana,at lvl 20 you start killing aviaks or the hermit.For most wizards,they go to South Karana and get exp of soloing the hermit.I am serious,these things give out great money too. ;)But once you stop at level 27,when we are passed that chapter lol...<BR>
                   Chapter 6<BR>
               25-30 is even better!<BR>
   As I was saying,once you stop at 27,forget about the hermit.It is green to you,you must now worry about the gnolls :) You must get in a group and root and blast right until lvl 29,you get to teleport people! But not while fighting unless they gonna pay you maybe lol!And once you get to 30,you still level at gnolls place until level 35.And at lvl 35 you can sit down and med without your book! <BR>
<BR>
               That's all folks!
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
